{
 "name": "RPlog_Toil_and_Trouble",
 "title": "Toil and Trouble: Ransacked on Bespin",
 "summary": "Arriving for dinner at Ylsa's immaculate Bespin apartment, the Corellian Paul finds the door's lock broken and the home violently ransacked. He surprises and knocks out a Rodian thug still searching the bedroom, then discovers Ylsa unconscious, beaten, and bare on the floor with cracked ribs. Paul tends her wounds, secures the apartment, and learns the attackers were men of her employer Ullo--one of them a high-ranking human who has assaulted her before--hunting for something of value she has been withholding from him. Refusing medical facilities for fear of Imperial scrutiny of her 'distinctive blood,' Ylsa is bandaged, sedated, and carried to Paul's ship the Wing, where he treats and bathes her. As she finally drifts into safe sleep, Paul quietly resolves to free her from Ullo, suspecting the thugs were after the rare Tamisian book she gave him, and stays up copying its contents before it must be surrendered.",
